  "body": "/kind bug\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\n[OpenShift's fluentd container](https://github.com/openshift/openshift-ansible/blob/master/roles/openshift_logging_fluentd/templates/2.x/fluentd.j2#L222) collects logs from other docker containers and thus mounts `/var/lib/docker/containers` as HostPath volume.\r\n\r\n`/var/lib/docker/containers` is intentionally mounted by Docker with `private` mount propagation and thus conflicts with Kubernetes trying to mount this directory as rslave when running the container:\r\n\r\n```\r\nError: failed to start container \"fluentd-elasticsearch\": Error response from daemon: linux mounts: Path /var/lib/docker/containers is mounted on /var/lib/docker/containers but it is not a shared or slave mount.\r\n```\r\n\r\nMountPropagation does not allow to fall back to `private`, it supports only rshared and rslave, so there is no way how to mount `/var/lib/docker/containers` into pods now.\r\n\r\n/sig storage\r\n/sig node",
